The Police Command in Enugu State says  the abducted Permanent Secretary in Enugu State Ministry of Lands, Mr Augustine Udeh, has regained freedom.<img class="size-full wp-image-1244839 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=640%2C408&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police" width="640" height="408" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=300%2C191&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=768%2C490&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=1024%2C653&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=58%2C37&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=260%2C166&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=200%2C128&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?resize=560%2C357&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Police-debunk-rumour-of-bomb-explosion-in-Enugu-State-Police.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Command’s Public Relations Officer, SP Ebere Amaraizu, revealed this on Tuesday in a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Enugu. Amaraizu said the  abductors bowed to pressure mounted as a result of joint operations of security operatives leading to  letting  the perm. sec.  off the hook. 14-year Enugu girl was with boyfriend, not kidnapped – Police(Opens in a new browser tab) “Udeh was allegedly abducted on Aug. 25 along Ituku-Awgu axis of the Enugu-Port Harcourt Expressway. “Following his abduction, security operatives had been on the trail until today, Aug. 27,’’ the police spokesman said. The police spokesman said that  manhunt was still on towards unmasking his abductors who hurriedly left him off the hook as security operatives were closing-in on them, adding that they absconded to avoid being nabbed at Ogbaku forest. “A full scale investigation has been intensified into the incident,’’ he added. (NAN). Vanguard The Police Command in Enugu State has rescued an abducted Enugu-based Catholic priest without payment of ransom as demanded by his abductors. July 10, 2018 In "News" Abductors of Sheik Adam Idoko, the Chief Imam of the University of Nigeria, Nsukka, UNN, Central Mosque have released him at the wee hours of this morning. September 17, 2015 In "News" The Police Command in Enugu State on Saturday rescued abducted Prof. Nduka Eya unhurt while one of the suspects involved in the kidnap was arrested. August 5, 2017 In "News"